<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">McCormick</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-19"><hi rend="italic">February 19,
                                    1904</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay informs Mr. McCormick that the United States Government
                            considers the reply of the Russian Government as responsive to the
                            proposal of this Government and will at once communicate it to the
                            Governments of China and Japan, which have already signified their
                            adherence to the principles of the proposal.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>